 result‚Üêobject Hide arg;was;new
‚çù Hide a GUI object

 was‚Üêobject._visible
 :If was>0 ‚çù Is it visible?
     :If 0=object._opened ‚çù Is it a closed object?
         ‚çù We have to run the Open method first, before we do anything else
         object('Open'##.Invoke)‚ç¨ ‚çù Force it open
         was‚Üêobject._visible ‚çù In case it changed
         :If was‚â§0 ‚çù Is it hidden now?
             :Return ‚çù Nothing left to do so just exit
         :EndIf
     :EndIf

     ‚çù Negate the APL+Win visible property
     new‚Üê(-was)+object._class‚â°'Menu' ‚çù Menu objects can't be ¬Ø1
     object._visible‚Üênew ‚çù Store the new APL+Win value

     ‚çù And update Dyalog to change the actual screen
     object ##.‚àÜWSet‚äÇ'Visible' 0 ‚çù Set Dyalog control visibility
 :EndIf

